      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative agreement metric (e.g., NRMSE) reported with statistical confidence intervals; systematic bias assessed across all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Qualitative graphical comparison provided; no quantitative agreement metric with confidence intervals is reported. Systematic over-prediction at high-shear operating points is noted but not formally characterized. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstrated that the CFD-predicted hemolysis index is the direct clinical decision variable; mapping from model output to regulatory threshold documented.",
      "rationale": "The NIH is the intended regulatory QoI, but the mapping from CFD shear-stress integration to NIH involves an empirical power-law model with coefficients derived from non-VAD literature. Applicability to VAD shear environments is not established. Achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
